cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with designing algorithms for graph problems, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of color coding as a technique indicates a possible fit with cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), while the mention of planar graphs suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category. Finally, the use of splitters and hash families points towards cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible category.
